runs.comm: and he has been crunched away for four first ball. This is a wide length ball, and Finch gets stuck into it
gets the inswinger going this time, beats the inside edge, hits the pad, but this is headed down leg
another inswinger... this starts from outside leg, squares him up as Warner defends
another inswinger, ending towards the off stump, defended back to him from the crease
this is pitched well outside leg, and goes for a leg-bye
big inswinger, beats the inside edge again, and is headed down leg again
short of a length, just outside off, just pushes it defensively, and it flies off the bat and between mid-off and extra cover
throws his bat at this length ball on off, ends up slicing it, but there s a deep cover placed, which means there is a gap in the circle, and that is exactly where this ball goes
short of a length, seams away from middle and off, beats him as he defends
full, middle and off, driven to mid-off for one
short of a length, tucked away off the hip for a single
short of a length, middle and off, defended with an open face
seams away from around off, pushed to point
makes slight room, punches this on the up, can't beat extra cover
short of a length, no room, not too straight, and all Finch can do is tap it back to BK
slower ball, 118ks, on a length, middle and leg, Finch is caught deep in the crease trying to make room. Hence can't make the adjustment
short of a length, outside off, smashed to mid-off for one
length ball going across Warner, who wants to hit it over mid-off. Beaten by the angle
carrom ball and he pushes it to the off side
this was miscued! Tossed up by Ashwin and Finch gets on his knee looking to slog, gets the top edge behind the bowler, Kohli jogs from mid-on and takes the skier
flatter delivery on the pads and he works it to the on side
full outside off and driven to the on side
as straight as it gets! Tossed up by Ashwin, Warner gets well forward and lofts him straight down the ground
full outside off and driven to cover
keeps it nice and straight and he punches it back to the bowler
that's two batsmen caught within the circle, this was pitched up outside off and he looked to clear the infield, mistimed it and Jadeja took it jogging a few yards to his left from mid-off
good length outside off and punched towards cover point
once again doesn't give him room, he nudges it off his pads and the keeper collects
Watson cramped for room again as he can only knock it back to the bowler
he stays beside the line and dabs it to third man

Was he bowled or not? Dhoni was up to the stumps, Mohit cramped Watson for room as he looked to angle it to third man, the ball came in and the leg lights were flashing, even Dhoni wasn't sure if the ball deflected off him to the stumps instead, Watson stands his ground and the umpires check with the third umpire, it's confirmed that the ball hit the top of the stumps first
this was a short one and he decided rather late to upper cut but missed
slower ball nudged to the on side
not very convincing, this was angled across and he punched it half heartedly and the ball was spooned into the gap at point
comes forward and he punches it to the off side
he stays back and punches it to the covers
flatter one and he gets on his knee and mistimes the sweep
gets down for the slog early and forces it to deep midwiket
stabs at it and he pinches a single to cover
flat! This was tossed up on the pads and he gets on his knee quickly and bludgeons it over deep midwicket
this was high and over the rope! Raina pitched this on a good length but it was on the pads, that's Maxwell's hitting area - promptly slogs it over fine leg
works it away to deep midwicket
fullish on the pads and he clips it to deep midwicket
a fidgety Warner comes down the track and checks his shot, works it to the on side
flatter one and he works it to midwicket
the impatience gets to Warner! He tries to break free, gets on his knee to slog but mistimes it to behind midwicket, Rohit runs forward from deep midwicket and hangs on falling forward
he goes back at the crease and thumps it just wide of cover
quicker and flatter and worked to deep midwicket
slip in place, comes on slow and he punches it to the off side
Maxwell and deep midwicket - inseparable, Jadeja errs by tossing it on the pads and he sends it several rows over the rope
it's in the air but over the off side and lands short of deep point
stays back and punches it to the off side
pushed through a bit quicker and he looks to cut but misses
he tosses this one wide down the leg side

freak dismissal for Maxwell! Ashwin comes round the wicket, Maxwell gets cheeky and looks to play the reverse sweep, he gets in position but the execution was all haywire, exposed all three stumps and it was the carrom ball that shaved the leg stu,p, he was on the floor after losing balance
tossed up and he gets forward to defend
pushes a full delivery to mid-on
he looks to cut but misses
beaten again, this is good bowling and the pressure really telling on Australia
tucked away to the leg side
straight! Tossed up by Jadeja, Bailey makes room and comes down the wicket and lofts him over long-off
the captain goes, Bailey tries to clear the rope again but perishes, this was tossed on middle and he slogged but found deep midwicket
gets forward and punches it to the off side
comes forward and punches it to the off side
rocks back and cuts down to point
Mishra starts off with a short one, pulled in front of square
pushes a full one down to long-on
gets forward and drives him to the off side
gets forward and takes an easy single to point
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
good running again, pushes at it with soft hands towards cover and calls early
flatter one and he clips it to the on side
tossed up and he gets forward and defends
tossed up on middle and leg, he lofts down the ground and didn't look in control, placed it wide of long-on
looks to cut but misses
gets forward and drives back to the bowler
slightly shorter and he pushes it to deep cover
yet another Australian perishes to the slog! This time it's Haddin trying to slog against the turn and it's miscued towards deep square leg, Bhubi holds on
he stays back and punches it down the track
flatter one and he drills it down the ground
gives it a bit more air and he drills it to deep cover
swivels and pulls him to fine leg
fires that fuller and flatter and clipped behind square

Appeal for a run out and Starc's in trouble! Hodge worked this to point and set off but Starc had to hurry, the throw was to the keeper and the LED in the stumps lit up before Dhoni could gather and whip the bails, even when he broke the bails Starc was short of his ground so he was indeed out, the flashlight made it confusing though
another slog, another wicket, gets on his knee and plays against the turn, two men converge but Jadeja hangs on
gets forward and pushes it to the off side
punches it back to the bowler but wide of him, would have been a great catch
the sharp googly, he goes back and cuts against the turn
goes back and punches it down the ground to long-on
the carrom ball, didn't pick it and he chops it to the off side
Dhoni takes the catch to complete the mauling, tossed up by Ashwin an.d Muirhead made room to cut, thick outside edge and Dhoni knew it
